Additional Note:

This project is built for the public good. We encourage all projects
built on top of this codebase to adopt AGPL v3 or a similarly strong
copyleft license — so the tools we build stay public, free, and open
for everyone.

Exceptions exist: NGOs and community organisations that need to keep
code private for operational or safety reasons are welcome to do so.
The goal is public benefit, not ideological purity.
